Northward Bound: The Road to Kochendorf

The gates of Ohnemenschen creak shut behind you as the company sets its sights north. The rugged terrain begins to soften, giving way to the rolling greens and tilled soil of the central heartlands.

The air smells of damp earth and blooming crops. After days of meager rations and salt-dried meat, the promise of Kochendorf hangs over the men like a morale boost. They say the village is prosperingwhich usually means the wine is cheap, the bread is soft, and the contracts are plenty.

Current Status

  • Location: Moving North towards Kochendorf.

  • Environment: Fertile farmland, clear roads.

  • Party Mood: Anticipatory.

As the thatched roofs of the village appear on the horizon, the brothers tighten their belts and shoulder their gear. The market square ahead looks bustling, even from this distance.

How do you want to approach the village? We can head straight for the Marketplace to resupply, check the Tavern for rumors, or head to the Village Elder to see if any contracts are pinned to the board.

Just outside of Ohnemenschen, we spotted a small group of 7 BRIGANDS A rough and tough band of raiders preying on the weak.  Some Bandit Rabble, A Bandit Rabble Poacher, A Possessed Arbalester. We of course would not let them live. AH! Juicy experience points.

Victory on the Road

Short-lived was the brigands' ambition! They thought they found prey, but they only found their graves. In just four rounds, the company systematically dismantled the raiders. Necola the Silver Sword led the charge with a devastating 230 damage, while the rest of the line held firm, ensuring the Possessed Arbalester didn't cause any lasting havoc.

The skirmish served as a perfect warm-up for the road ahead. Aside from Theudebald F taking a significant hit to his armor (or skin), the company emerges largely unscathed and a bit more experienced.

Battle Aftermath

  • The MVP: Necola the Silver Sword with a clean kill and massive damage output.

  • Wounded: Theudebald F (59 damage taken) and Harun D Al-Baji (minor scrapes).

  • Status: The road to Kochendorf is now slightly saferand your pockets slightly heavier.

With the blood cleaned from your blades and the crows descending on the "Bandit Rabble," the fertile fields of Kochendorf finally loom close.

Would you like to stop to repair Theudebald's gear before entering the village, or shall we head straight into the market to see what rewards your victory might buy?

A Fever Dream in the Dark

The crackle of the campfire usually brings comfort, but tonight it brought a waking nightmare. The sight of Wilfried B transformed into a human torch by a tiny, "trusting" spider was vivid enough to make your skin crawl. Necolas sudden phobia and the smell of burning hair felt all too realuntil the embers cleared.

Finding Wilfried B sitting there, perfectly intact and utterly confused by your shouting, is a jarring reminder of the toll the road takes on a Captains mind. Or perhaps, as that white shadow suggests, something more ethereal is stalking the company's periphery.

Night Watch Report

  • Morale: Shaken (for you, at least). The men seem oblivious.

  • Casualties: None (physical). Wilfried B is alive and well, if a bit puzzled.

  • Observation: A "white shadow" sighted. Could be exhaustion... or a lingering presence.

The sun rises on Day 27. The nightmares of the night fade as the morning mist lifts, revealing the sturdy palisades and bustling outskirts of Kochendorf. The smell of fresh bread from the village ovens is a welcome replacement for the smell of phantom smoke.

Would you like to head to the marketplace to stock up on that fresh food, or go straight to the village center to see if anyone has seen any "white shadows" or has work for a band of seasoned mercenaries?

Just outside of Kochendorf...

---

The forests of the north are a primeval place, the span of a life is measured in months and the climate is a perpetual state of autumn or winter where the wildlife is as deadly as the weather. Leaving the town to walk through these forests is humbling - the trees here have outlived but the gods themselves, or so some would say. Your thoughts begin to wander further as the bridle path begins to feel endless and the trees curl inwards. The pressure builds in your head as you fall to the ground. The brush parts for a woman clad in furs holding a staff, focusing intently on you as you try to regain your balance. The noise stops and your mind clears. The woman speaks.  "Why are you here, outsider?"  Her brow furrows and she hums, but her lips part again.

"I know what you are, and I know what you have done. Not just in this life - but the ones that have come before."  Her gaze lifts as she loses focus with you and looks down the path, deep in contemplation. The weight in your mind begins to lift as a tide ebbs before it comes crashing back. However, as she fixes her gaze with yours, the wave doesn't come crashing back. It is still there, at the back of your head - restrained like a warhound on a chain.  "Something is changing outsider - something is coming that we can't stand alone and face. I do not care for your work, your motivations or hardships. I care about stopping the cataclysm of what is to come." "Welcome to the Usurper's Bane," I said.

Besides the ability to inscribe objects with magical rune sigils she also knows sorcerous incantations in the form of chants, and can induce trance states through which she may perceive and interact with the spirit world and the spirits therein.

The Seer Joins the Fold

The air grows heavy and the woods turn silent as Maike steps from the shadows of the ancient northern timber. Her words cut through the mundane concerns of crowns and contracts, reaching back into lives you barely remember. She isn't here for gold or glory; she is here for the Usurper's Bane and the storm that gathers on the horizon.

With her arrival, the company gains more than just a fighter. You now have a Valaa mistress of runes and spirits who can bolster your gear with sigils and command the very essence of the battlefield through her chants.

New Companion: Maike the Vala

The "white shadow" from your campfire dream suddenly feels much more significant with a spirit-talker now among your ranks.

Kochendorf is now just a stone's throw away. With Maike's arrival, the stakes of your journey have shifted from simple merc work to something far more ancient.

Would you like to enter Kochendorf and see if the Vala needs specific supplies for her inscriptions, or shall we look for a contract to test her chants in live combat?

The Gift of the Geist

You find Necola sitting on a whetstone, her bandages seeped with fresh red. She looks at the vial, then up at you, her silver eyes narrowing. She knows what this isa chance to bridge the gap between human limitation and the supernatural speed of the ghosts you fought.

"You want me to drink that?" she asks, a ghost of a smirk playing on her lips despite her wounds. "I already fight like a demon, Captain. You trying to make me look like one, too?"

She takes the vial. If anyones constitution can handle the strain of a mutation, its the Silver Sword.

Midday Status: Day 28

  • The Mutation: Necola has the Geist Mutagen. (Depending on your internal rules, this could grant her a massive boost to Initiative, the ability to pass through zones of control, or a terrifying presence that breaks enemy morale).

  • Company Condition: * Repairs: Nearly complete. The smell of oil and whetstones fills the air.

    • Thordis: Watching the process with grim fascination. Hes never seen a Captain who experiments on his own lieutenants.

    • Zombie Theudebald: Still standing where you left him, a silent sentinel in the noon sun.

The men are rested, and the purse is heavy. With the Mutagen administered and the gear repaired, we are at a crossroads.

What shall we do with our afternoon in Kochendorf?

  • The Marketplace: We haven't spent that 5,500+ crown windfall yet. Shall we buy some Top-Tier Armor for our front line?

  • Lady Amelia's Drill: Have the Swordmaster put Thordis and the others through a rigorous training session to sharpen their "mathematics"?

Session 9 Wrap-Up: The Price of Power

What a session! Youve transitioned from a band of mercenaries into a force dealing with the truly supernatural. The Usurper's Bane is wealthier, deadlier, and stranger than ever before.

The Companys Evolution

  • New Recruits: You added the mystical Maike (Vala), the legendary Lady Amelia (Swordmaster), and the vengeful Thordis (Arbalester) to your ranks.

  • The Mutation: You spent the night in gruesome study to produce a Geist Mutagen, granting Necola the Silver Sword powers that blur the line between human and spirit.

  • The "Fodder": Theudebald remains with the company, though his soul is gonehe now serves as a mindless Wiederganger shield for his former brothers.

Major Engagements

  1. The Brigand Skirmish: A quick, efficient slaughter north of Ohnemenschen.

  2. The Kochendorf Infestation: A massive purge of 20+ Nachzehrers and their kin, earning the town's trust and a solid 800 crowns.

  3. The Remote Graveyard: A harrowing 11-round battle against Geists and Possessed Nobles. Though victorious, the cost was the life of Hiltrude and the "death" of Theudebald.

Logistics & Economy

  • Massive Windfall: You successfully completed the contract for Raginari, leaving you with a staggering treasury surplus (nearly 7,000 crowns earned this session alone).

  • Location: Camped outside Kochendorf on the afternoon of Day 28.

  • Status: Gear is repaired, wounds are binding, and the men are battle-hardened.

The Usurper's Bane has survived the aetherium, but the "cataclysm" Maike warned of still looms on the horizon.

Next time we pick up, shall we spend that mountain of gold in the Kochendorf markets, or is it time to move out and see where the Valas path leads us?
